Edward III. laid the Foundation of our Riches, by the Eſtabliſhment of our Woollen Manufactures in England;

   Triceſimo ſeptimo Ed. 3. cap. 9 to the carrying on of which Noble Deſign of his, he ſtrictly injoyn'd the Wear of our Woollen Manufactures, by ſeveral Ranks and Degrees of People by Sumptuary Laws: He took exact care that Merchants Aliens,
   Triceſim. octavo Edw. 3. cap. 2. who ſold any Commodities in England, ſhould inveſt the Money upon the Growth of this Kingdom; And by his wiſe Conduct in theſe Affairs, he made a conſiderable Advance in the Riches and Glory of England in a few Years.
